1
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:38,960
=Adventure behind the Bronze Door=

2
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,900
(Adapted from the original novel
"Zang Hai Hua" by Nan Pai San Shu)

3
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:44,180
(This story is purely fictional)
=Episode 2=

4
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:47,870
(The kid who appeared out of nowhere)

5
00:01:47,870 --> 00:01:49,950
(took Ma Pingchuan
to the backside of the mountain.)

6
00:01:50,269 --> 00:01:53,230
(Ma Pingchuan looked in
the direction the child was looking)

7
00:01:54,749 --> 00:01:56,150
(and was shocked.)

8
00:01:58,629 --> 00:01:59,629
A scorpion?

9
00:02:02,870 --> 00:02:03,909
What's this?

10
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:06,469
Under this area

11
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:08,509
lies the ruins of a town

12
00:02:08,509 --> 00:02:10,590
that was buried
by a mudslide many years ago.

13
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:13,150
The extent of what you see

14
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,669
is the extent of the ruins.

15
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:18,469
The town was built
into the weird shape of a scorpion.

16
00:02:18,990 --> 00:02:20,789
The grass here dies

17
00:02:21,189 --> 00:02:22,430
because of the defense mechanism

18
00:02:22,430 --> 00:02:23,590
that was put in place

19
00:02:23,789 --> 00:02:25,349
when the town was built.

20
00:02:25,749 --> 00:02:26,909
If someone gets inside,

21
00:02:26,909 --> 00:02:28,110
the switch will be triggered,

22
00:02:28,550 --> 00:02:30,110
causing the gas in the machinery

23
00:02:30,349 --> 00:02:31,749
to evaporate greatly.

24
00:02:32,430 --> 00:02:33,390
All plants on the ground

25
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:34,870
will be poisoned to death

26
00:02:35,749 --> 00:02:36,990
overnight.

27
00:02:38,509 --> 00:02:39,430
Punk.

28
00:02:40,110 --> 00:02:41,430
Although I don't quite understand,

29
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:42,909
don't trick me.

30
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:45,229
Do you have X-ray vision?

31
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:48,110
Because I'm the one who went down.

32
00:02:53,189 --> 00:02:54,550
The ruin beneath us

33
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:56,710
has eaten up all the coffins

34
00:02:57,310 --> 00:02:58,469
in your ancestral tombs.

35
00:02:58,870 --> 00:02:59,789
What do you mean?

36
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:02,390
Is the ruins alive?

37
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:06,150
If you dig the deeper areas,

38
00:03:06,469 --> 00:03:07,509
you'll find

39
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:09,430
that all the coffins

40
00:03:09,949 --> 00:03:12,390
has sunk
into the outer wall of the ruins.

41
00:03:13,909 --> 00:03:16,110
It's like
they're attracted by something.

42
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:22,669
There's one more thing

43
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:24,870
I think I need to tell you.

44
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:28,069
There will be no grass
growing within dozens of miles of here

45
00:03:28,069 --> 00:03:29,349
in a few months.

46
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:31,110
Everyone in this area

47
00:03:31,229 --> 00:03:32,550
will die miserably.

48
00:03:33,110 --> 00:03:35,550
Punk, don't play tricks on me.

49
00:03:39,629 --> 00:03:40,909
Sir.

50
00:03:42,550 --> 00:03:44,030
Put the guns down.

51
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:45,590
Put down the guns.

52
00:03:49,110 --> 00:03:50,310
I saw your coffins

53
00:03:50,550 --> 00:03:51,870
in the ruins.

54
00:03:52,270 --> 00:03:53,629
That's why I told you about it.

55
00:03:54,749 --> 00:03:56,669
I want you to do two things for me

56
00:03:56,669 --> 00:03:58,030
within two hours.

57
00:03:58,390 --> 00:03:59,189
First,

58
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,669
prepare a short knife
weighing three kilograms,

59
00:04:01,789 --> 00:04:03,590
lamp oil wicks
and a bag of charcoal powder.

60
00:04:04,180 --> 00:04:05,310
And think of a way to seal up

61
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:06,789
several holes in the ruins.

62
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:07,990
Second,

63
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:10,229
at the edge of this area,

64
00:04:10,490 --> 00:04:11,909
take a five-zhang-long bamboo pole,

65
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:14,069
fill it with lime,
and hammer it into the mud,

66
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,990
leaving only a finger-length.

67
00:04:16,270 --> 00:04:17,349
The denser the better.

68
00:04:17,989 --> 00:04:19,390
Why are we doing that?

69
00:04:19,669 --> 00:04:20,750
If I don't come out

70
00:04:21,030 --> 00:04:21,989
after seven days,

71
00:04:22,789 --> 00:04:23,789
please send this letter

72
00:04:24,150 --> 00:04:25,789
back to my hometown for me.

73
00:04:28,180 --> 00:04:29,620
(To The Zhang Family)

74
00:04:35,909 --> 00:04:36,750
Sir.

75
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:37,909
Sir.

76
00:04:39,549 --> 00:04:40,669
Everything's ready.

77
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:49,750
Young man.

78
00:04:51,469 --> 00:04:53,989
The kid left and never came back.

79
00:04:54,349 --> 00:04:55,630
Later, Ma Pingchuan sent someone

80
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:57,750
to the address
on the letter the kid gave him

81
00:04:57,909 --> 00:05:00,390
and found it to be a huge mansion.

82
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:02,309
But it's already empty.

83
00:05:02,429 --> 00:05:04,669
No one knows where the kid went.

84
00:05:04,669 --> 00:05:05,950
And no one knows

85
00:05:05,950 --> 00:05:07,869
if there's
a scorpion-shaped ruin underneath.

86
00:05:07,869 --> 00:05:09,789
Is the kid
that Ma Pingchuan talked about

87
00:05:11,070 --> 00:05:12,109
Qiling?

88
00:05:12,109 --> 00:05:13,190
It must be.

89
00:05:18,349 --> 00:05:19,390
Ma'an Village.

90
00:05:20,710 --> 00:05:22,190
Does this place still exist?

91
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:23,190
Of course.

92
00:05:23,309 --> 00:05:24,390
They had already

93
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:26,070
dug the withered area

94
00:05:26,229 --> 00:05:28,270
and didn't find
the so-called scorpion-shaped ruins.

95
00:05:29,349 --> 00:05:30,909
All they found are these agate beads.

96
00:05:31,830 --> 00:05:33,549
Later, Ma Pingchuan suddenly decided

97
00:05:34,150 --> 00:05:35,610
to move his family from Ma'an Village

98
00:05:36,469 --> 00:05:37,510
and go to Nilaisi.

99
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,070
Nilaisi?

100
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:41,070
Yes, a small country
outside the borders.

101
00:05:41,590 --> 00:05:42,349
Specifically,

102
00:05:42,349 --> 00:05:44,549
they went to Dejia,
the capital of Nilaisi.

103
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:46,109
Near Mosang's snow mountain.

104
00:05:46,229 --> 00:05:48,270
My informant just came back
from there two days ago

105
00:05:48,270 --> 00:05:50,070
and saw many of their ancestral items

106
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:52,190
piled up in front of their house.

107
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:53,750
They were being sold at a low price.

108
00:05:55,150 --> 00:05:57,309
There were a lot of those beads.

109
00:05:58,030 --> 00:05:59,869
They're good stuff.

110
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:01,030
Is that so?

111
00:06:01,309 --> 00:06:02,190
Sure.

112
00:06:03,390 --> 00:06:04,469
Give me the address.

113
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:06,109
I'll take a look when I have time.

114
00:06:09,109 --> 00:06:10,349
Third Master.

115
00:06:11,150 --> 00:06:12,109
Having said that,

116
00:06:12,549 --> 00:06:14,469
we finally got to the point.

117
00:06:15,109 --> 00:06:16,270
If you're going there,

118
00:06:16,989 --> 00:06:18,070
bring me with you.

119
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:20,150
We're familiar.

120
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:21,360
I can give you a counteroffer.

121
00:06:21,590 --> 00:06:22,830
With our money

122
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:24,309
your influence,

123
00:06:24,590 --> 00:06:25,669
and my help,

124
00:06:25,909 --> 00:06:26,909
let's make a deal.

125
00:06:27,590 --> 00:06:28,590
Jin Wantang.

126
00:06:28,789 --> 00:06:31,309
You're still trying
to trick me into this, aren't you?

127
00:06:33,789 --> 00:06:35,590
My dear.

128
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:37,590
Why can't you tell the difference?

129
00:06:37,989 --> 00:06:39,669
We're on the same boat.

130
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:43,630
Leave.

131
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:44,469
Leave.

132
00:06:44,469 --> 00:06:45,190
Third Master.

133
00:06:45,190 --> 00:06:47,390
What are you doing?

134
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:49,789
I just want to make some money.

135
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:51,390
I swear

136
00:06:51,549 --> 00:06:52,549
my shop will burn down

137
00:06:52,549 --> 00:06:54,549
and I can never find anything good
if I trick you.

138
00:06:54,549 --> 00:06:55,510
Are you happy now?

139
00:06:56,789 --> 00:06:58,590
You're daring to say that.

140
00:06:59,429 --> 00:07:00,989
You want to trick me to abroad.

141
00:07:01,270 --> 00:07:02,429
I don't know anyone there.

142
00:07:02,549 --> 00:07:03,549
If someone killed me,

143
00:07:03,549 --> 00:07:04,760
who's going to collect my body?

144
00:07:04,989 --> 00:07:07,030
You'd better get going. Leave.

145
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:07,909
Third Master!

146
00:07:11,150 --> 00:07:13,590
You really won't take action
without a clear target.

147
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:22,349
My informant

148
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:24,429
took this photo at their doorstep.

149
00:07:24,429 --> 00:07:25,669
Could there be a mistake?

150
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:38,070
Did I really accuse you
unfairly this time?

151
00:07:41,349 --> 00:07:42,950
All right, stop sighing.

152
00:07:44,909 --> 00:07:45,789
Let's go together.

153
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,309
When are we leaving?

154
00:07:49,390 --> 00:07:50,469
Did you bring your ID card?

155
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:53,270
To book tickets.

156
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:56,460
We'll fly to a border city first
and find a way to leave the country.

157
00:07:57,869 --> 00:07:58,869
It's

158
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:00,469
settled then.

159
00:08:00,549 --> 00:08:01,549
It's settled.

160
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:09,070
I'll let you know

161
00:08:09,429 --> 00:08:10,669
as soon as I booked the tickets.

162
00:08:10,789 --> 00:08:11,669
All right.

163
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:23,309
Boss.

164
00:08:23,630 --> 00:08:24,830
Wang Meng, where are you?

165
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:25,510
Home.

166
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,370
Your leave is canceled.
Come back to work immediately.

167
00:08:27,390 --> 00:08:28,270
Boss.

168
00:08:28,669 --> 00:08:30,510
I finally saved up enough leaves.

169
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:32,470
Just let me play games at home.

170
00:08:33,709 --> 00:08:34,870
Jin Wantang stopped by.

171
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:37,589
That old jerk

172
00:08:37,589 --> 00:08:38,709
told you a story,

173
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:40,589
so you're going to Dejia with him?

174
00:08:40,709 --> 00:08:43,110
Why do I have the feeling
that it's a scam?

175
00:08:43,110 --> 00:08:44,189
Even you could tell,

176
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:45,870
how could I not tell?

177
00:08:46,069 --> 00:08:47,630
You have more reason not to go.

178
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:49,870
I'm going. I'm definitely going.

179
00:08:51,829 --> 00:08:52,909
So far

180
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:55,110
it's the only clue related to Qiling.

181
00:08:55,189 --> 00:08:57,789
If I want to understand Qiling's past,
I have to go to Dejia

182
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,270
and find the Ma family's descendants.

183
00:08:59,589 --> 00:09:00,870
I've packed my luggage.

184
00:09:01,069 --> 00:09:02,630
Keep your ID card safe.

185
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:03,870
Don't let Jin Wantang find it.

186
00:09:05,030 --> 00:09:05,990
Also,

187
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:07,510
Come back soon.

188
00:09:07,870 --> 00:09:08,630
Bye.

189
00:09:23,289 --> 00:09:23,923
(Wuzhou)

190
00:09:37,901 --> 00:09:38,720
(Dejia)

191
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:45,340
(Dejia)

192
00:10:47,470 --> 00:10:48,510
Sir, excuse me.

193
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:50,709
May I ask a question?

194
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:55,829
Welcome.

195
00:11:55,990 --> 00:11:56,909
Sir.

196
00:11:56,990 --> 00:11:58,270
What would you like?

197
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:01,829
Boss,

198
00:12:02,069 --> 00:12:03,309
I want to ask you something.

199
00:12:03,870 --> 00:12:05,350
Did the family across the street

200
00:12:05,549 --> 00:12:06,829
move somewhere?

201
00:12:06,990 --> 00:12:08,069
The Ma family?

202
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:09,230
Do you know them?

203
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,510
How are you related to them?

204
00:12:10,589 --> 00:12:11,709
Why are you looking for him?

205
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:16,990
Here's the thing.

206
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:18,510
I'm

207
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:20,990
also in the antique business in Wuzhou.

208
00:12:21,510 --> 00:12:23,350
I ordered a batch of goods
from the Ma family.

209
00:12:23,789 --> 00:12:25,709
I've made all the payment,

210
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:26,589
but I couldn't

211
00:12:26,589 --> 00:12:27,390
get in touch with them

212
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,750
when I called them some time ago.

213
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,189
I had to come over myself.

214
00:12:30,189 --> 00:12:31,030
Who knew

215
00:12:31,110 --> 00:12:32,429
they're gone?

216
00:12:32,549 --> 00:12:33,390
So do you know

217
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:34,549
where they went?

218
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:35,829
Could you tell me something?

219
00:12:35,829 --> 00:12:37,189
Did they rip you off too?

220
00:12:37,189 --> 00:12:38,110
Yeah.

221
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:40,309
Those jerks

222
00:12:40,630 --> 00:12:42,230
had always owed me a lot of money.

223
00:12:42,350 --> 00:12:43,669
They had some conscience

224
00:12:43,709 --> 00:12:45,069
before they left.

225
00:12:45,069 --> 00:12:46,309
They didn't leave secretly.

226
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:48,870
They gave me all his family antiques.

227
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:50,350
In that case,

228
00:12:50,909 --> 00:12:52,110
are these things

229
00:12:52,709 --> 00:12:54,030
and that mirror

230
00:12:54,069 --> 00:12:55,350
from the Ma family?

231
00:12:58,429 --> 00:13:00,110
You're quite lucky.

232
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:01,230
At least you recovered some costs.

233
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:02,390
Look at me.

234
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:03,429
Could you

235
00:13:03,429 --> 00:13:04,390
please tell me

236
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:05,549
where they went

237
00:13:05,549 --> 00:13:07,110
so I can collect my debt?

238
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:09,750
I heard

239
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:12,350
their whole family moved to

240
00:13:12,829 --> 00:13:14,549
Mosang. Yes.

241
00:13:15,150 --> 00:13:17,390
When the Ma family's business was good,

242
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:19,510
they often went there to purchase goods.

243
00:13:20,429 --> 00:13:21,669
I heard

244
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:24,350
the antiques there are very cheap.

245
00:13:24,350 --> 00:13:25,549
It's just that I'm old

246
00:13:25,549 --> 00:13:26,909
and weak.

247
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:29,110
Otherwise, I really want to
go there to pick up some goods.

248
00:13:29,270 --> 00:13:30,909
The antique business

249
00:13:30,990 --> 00:13:32,189
is so difficult now.

250
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:33,189
All right.

251
00:13:33,390 --> 00:13:34,549
Thank you.

252
00:13:34,549 --> 00:13:36,230
I wish you a booming business.

253
00:13:46,669 --> 00:13:47,510
Wang Meng.

254
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,110
Boss.

255
00:13:48,429 --> 00:13:50,030
Sort out the funds in the store

256
00:13:50,150 --> 00:13:51,390
and transfer them all to my account.

257
00:13:51,390 --> 00:13:52,429
I'm going to Mosang.

258
00:13:52,949 --> 00:13:53,470
No.

259
00:13:53,470 --> 00:13:54,909
Boss, the store has run out of money.

260
00:13:55,230 --> 00:13:57,110
Besides, aren't you
looking for clues about Qiling?

261
00:13:57,189 --> 00:13:58,429
Why are you going to Mosang?

262
00:13:58,429 --> 00:13:59,829
That Jin jerk

263
00:13:59,829 --> 00:14:01,270
really tricked me.

264
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:03,429
The Ma family has long since left,

265
00:14:03,669 --> 00:14:04,669
but fortunately,

266
00:14:04,669 --> 00:14:06,230
I found some new clues.

267
00:14:06,350 --> 00:14:07,750
So I'm going to Mosang

268
00:14:08,189 --> 00:14:10,189
and see if there are
any business opportunities.

269
00:14:10,270 --> 00:14:10,909
Boss.

270
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,870
Why don't you hurry back?

271
00:14:13,110 --> 00:14:14,510
You know the situation of the store.

272
00:14:14,510 --> 00:14:15,870
We can't even afford
the water and electricity bills.

273
00:14:15,870 --> 00:14:16,429
We don't have money.

274
00:14:16,429 --> 00:14:17,909
Which one of us is the boss?

275
00:14:18,870 --> 00:14:21,549
Hurry up
and sell the goods in the store.

276
00:14:21,709 --> 00:14:23,589
Stay in the store for the next two days
and don't go out.

277
00:14:23,589 --> 00:14:25,429
Wait for me
to mail the goods back to you.

278
00:14:25,549 --> 00:14:26,390
Bye.

279
00:14:41,108 --> 00:14:42,611
(Dejia)

280
00:14:48,361 --> 00:14:49,239
(Mosang)

281
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:53,500
(Mosang)

282
00:15:40,549 --> 00:15:42,069
Boss, have you arrived in Mosang?

283
00:15:42,390 --> 00:15:43,390
How's Mosang?

284
00:15:43,589 --> 00:15:44,990
I heard it's quite lively over there.

